REQUIREMENT\par
\fs22 USER REQUIREMENT : \b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Registration page \b0 : Page which user can register themselves. Registration page contain logo, and fields to add name, email, phone number, enter password, confirm password and register button. After clicking on register button the data entered by the user will save on the database if the phone number is already exist in data base then shows message 'already have an account with this phone number'.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b User verification \b0 : Verification is for makeing sure that the user is exactly who they are supposed to be. Once the user is add the number in the field given and click send otp button an otp is sendes to the entered phone number and after adding otp to the field where it is enter and click the verify button the user is verified in the database if and only if the entered otp is correct as the sended otp from the system otherwise the screen shows 'incorrect otp, please enter correct otp'.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Permission access \b0 : Asking the user about the permissions in their gadget which should be enabled for the functioning of the system. In this screen the privacy terms and policies are given and and a check box which should user agree after reading the privacy and policy the permission requirements. there is an allow button and deny button which user can select if they want to allow or deny permission.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Login page\b0  : In login page user should enter their username and password, then click the login button and the system verifies is the entered username and password is correct. If it is correct the user redirects to home page otherwise shows the message 'invalid username or password'. There is also a forgot password option which redirect the user to another page to recover password.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Password recovery \b0 : User should enter their registered phone number in the field for phone number and then click on the submit button then an otp sends to the phone number. User can enter the otp and click on recover password button then the password is send to registered phone number of the user. There is a login button which allows the user to redirect to the login page to continue login process.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Home page \b0 : Home page of the user is the page which user entered after click the login button in the login page. The data fetch from the database and shows the user which is correspond to the username and password. Access the functionalities such as profile, search, notification, payment, system logo, about (app information).\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Profile \b0 : User can add and edit their phone number (there is a verifiction otp verification done like the time of registraion) name, email, password (They are optional). Also user can delete their account.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Searching\b0  : This helps user to search cab availibility thus they can book cab. User can search cab by model, location. There is given the types of cab in search page and also they can search by giving their current location and destination once they on location then they can see the nearest cabs. Once the location is on then the user can enter their destination thus user can able to see the rate of each type of cab in there nearest location.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Notification : \b0 In notification page the user can see the notification about their booked cab and common notifications for the users from the management side. When the user books the cab the driver get a notification did he/she wants to accept the booking. If the driver is ready to accept the drive then they should choose the acceot button. When the driver accepts the request then a notification will be received by the user. If the driver denys the notification then the user will receive the message that 'this cab is unavailable right now'. \par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}\b Payment \b0 : This page allows the user to make payment for the cab they had booked. This page have various payment options such as cash, e-payment (gpay, phone pay, paytm, pay through bank payment apps). Once the user selected the payment option then the page redirects according to the payment method they choose.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\tab Cash - User can pay after completing the ride directly to the cab driver. To get an invoice \tab the user should enter an unique code of the cab which needs the system to ensure that the \tab user completed the payment.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\tx142\tab\tab E-payment - When the user select the upi app and click on the proceed payment button \tab\tab\tab the page will redirect to the app and thus the user can make payment through the apps. \tab\tab\tab Once the payment has done that data will save on database thus the invoice can be \tab\tab\tab created.\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\tx142\b Invoice\b0  : Invoice is the commercial document delivered by the user to the service delivered. After the payment done there is an button which user can click to get their invoice. The invoice document contain the details they have travelled such as, time, distance, depature and arrival, cab number, amount they have paid, normal rate per kilometer, tax details all are the above details should be fetched from the database.\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Deleting account \b0 : User can delete their account whenever they want. To delete their account there is an button in the profile page 'delete account'. Once the user request to delete their account then system ask conformation by asking the user to enter their password. The user can delete account permanently if and only if they are entered their password correctly in the field and click delete button. As per the systems privacy policy the data of user will not be deleted from the server.\par

